{"lemma":"مِغْزَلِ","slug":"مِغْزَلِ","root":"غ.ز.ل","root_slug":"غ-ز-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ز-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31814","n31815","n31816","n31817"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%BA%D9%92%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spindle"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Tool noun from the root غ ز ل (ḡ z l). But also vocalized مَغْزَل (maḡzal), as a noun of place, and مُغْزَل (muḡzal), as a passive participle of أَغْزَلَ (ʔaḡzala)."},"ipa":["/miɣ.zal/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31814","headword_ar":"مَغْزَلٌ","root":"gzl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"migozalN","text_ar":"مِغْزَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places:       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazalN","text_ar":"غَزَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n31815","headword_ar":"مُغْزَلٌ","root":"gzl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"migozalN","text_ar":"مِغْزَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n31816","headword_ar":"مُغْزِلٌ","root":"gzl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A doe gazelle"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a young one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n31817","headword_ar":"مِغْزَلٌ","root":"gzl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugozalN","text_ar":"مُغْزَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Th, S, O, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magozalN","text_ar":"مَغْزَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, O, K,) the first as pronounced by [the tribe of] Temeem, the second as pronounced by [that of] Keys, and the last the most rare, (TA,) or the second as pronounced by Temeem, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A spindle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing with which one spins:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, MA, O, Msb, K. KL:) Fr says that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugozalN","text_ar":"مُغْزَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the original form, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ugozila","text_ar":"اُغْزِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ it was made to turn round ” or “ revolve ” [or “ was twirled ”]; (S, TA;) but the dammeh was deemed by the Arabs difficult of pronunciation, and therefore they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"migozalN","text_ar":"مِغْزَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miSoHafN","text_ar":"مِصْحَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mixodaEN","text_ar":"مِخْدَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mijosadN","text_ar":"مِجْسَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miTorafN","text_ar":"مِطْرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to IAth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"migozalN","text_ar":"مِغْزَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"instrument"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one spins"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magozalN","text_ar":"مَغْزَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazol","text_ar":"غَزْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which means the act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spinning"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"span thread"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yard"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugozalN","text_ar":"مُغْزَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place in which"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or this may here mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazol","text_ar":"غَزْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spun thread"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yarn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is put:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magaAzilu","text_ar":"مَغَازِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (MA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEorY mino migozalK","text_ar":"اَعْرى مِنْ مِغْزَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a prov. [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More naked than a spindle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Meyd.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibu Algazali A^aDal~u mino saAqi migozalK","text_ar":"صَاحِبُ الغَزَلِ اَضَلُّ مِنْ سَاقِ مِغْزَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The practiser of the talk and actions"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"usual between the lover and the object of love is more erring than the shank"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pin"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a spindle"},{"kind":"text","text":"), of which the error is its [aiding in] clothing mankind while it is [itself] naked. (A, TA.) ―         -b2-  It is said in a book of certain of the Jews,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayokumo ka*aA","text_ar":"عَلَيْكُمْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waka*aA waruboEu Almigozali","text_ar":"وَكَذَا وَرُبْعُ المِغْزَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I pon you lie as due from you such and such things and"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fourth part of what your women have spun."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magaAzilu","text_ar":"مَغَازِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamad","text_ar":"عَمَد"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eumud","text_ar":"عُمُد"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) [app. meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upright wooden supports of the seat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"machine called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naworaj","text_ar":"نَوْرَج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which the reaped grain heaped together is thrashed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Fr","Th","S","O","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}